               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; a few lines on the incipit page of the sections of Texts I and II; incipit of the subsections of Texts I and II; two lines of the concluding formula of Text I (fol. 131vb), supplication note (fol. 155ra), the Trinitarian formula (fol. 255ra); names of the days of the week written in the upper margin of Text I (fols. 2r, 17r, 42r, 62r, 87r, 104v, 118r) and Text II (fols.: 132r, 152v, 173r, 194r, 216v, 234rb, 244v); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
The names of the donors are rubricated with strong vermilion.</rubric>
